Yes, exactly! Once the server selection is implemented, adding a new server will be as simple as:

    Open ServerConfig.cpp
    Add one entry to the server list:

cpp

{
    .name                    = "NewServer",
    .classFunctionOffset     = 0x50,   // find with Cheat Engine
    .singletonFunctionOffset = 0x10,   // almost always 0x10
    .onTextMessageOffset     = 0x14,   // almost always 0x14
    .onTalkOffset            = 0x10,   // almost always 0x10
    .lightHackOffset         = 0xAC,   // either 0xAC or 0xB0
},

    Rebuild the DLL

The only value you actually need to find per server is classFunctionOffset — everything else is almost always the same. You find it with Cheat Engine by:

    Injecting the DLL with debug logging enabled
    Watching what value gets captured in hooked_bindSingletonFunction
    Adjusting the offset until functions are captured correctly

So in practice adding a new server takes maybe 30 minutes of Cheat Engine work to find the one offset, then 2 minutes to add it to the code and rebuild.




