  ⏵⏵ bypass permissions on · 3 bashes · ↓ to manageShow more9:05 PMThe note about Exordion means:
Exordion uses a different internal pointer type called SmartPtr<T> (a struct with 2 fields: address + control block) instead of a simple uintptr_t pointer. The original code had a special #if BUILD_EXORDION branch that switched the pointer types for this reason.
Now that the compile-time branch was removed, Exordion's offsets will load correctly from the server selection, BUT if Exordion's client actually passes SmartPtr objects on the stack when calling game functions, the bot might crash or misbehave when running on Exordion because it's expecting a simple pointer but getting a 2-field struct.
In practice this means:

All other servers (Realera, Miracle, etc.) → will work fine ✅
Exordion → offsets load correctly, but may crash or not work properly when actually using bot functions ⚠️

To fix Exordion properly later, you'd need to add a usesSmartPtr flag to the ServerConfig struct and handle the SmartPtr layout in the code. But that's a separate task.
For now, rebuild the DLL and test with Realera — it should work fine. Exordion support can be fixed later when you need it.
